================================================================
5. Re-verifying this inventory
================================================================

    # Gradle side (jk1 Gradle License Report plugin via init script)
    ./gradlew --init-script scripts/license-report.init.gradle.kts \
        :runtime:checkLicense :jvmti-agent:checkLicense

    # Go side (go-licenses)
    go install github.com/google/go-licenses@latest
    (cd cli && go-licenses check ./... --disallowed_types=forbidden,restricted \
        --ignore=github.com/mattn/go-localereader)

    # Both at once
    scripts/check-licenses.sh

The --ignore flag for go-localereader is intentional: the v0.0.1 tag in the
Go module cache predates the LICENSE file that exists in the upstream
repository, so go-licenses can't auto-detect it. The full MIT license text
is reproduced verbatim in section 6 to satisfy the redistribution clause.

Allowed-license rules live in scripts/allowed-licenses.json. Adjust that
file if a new compatible license is intentionally introduced.

The full text of the Apache License 2.0 under which Forja is released is in
the LICENSE file at the project root (and mirrored at cli/LICENSE for
go-licenses to discover from within the Go module).

